\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 contains isolated points; for example, consider 
\begin_inset Formula $2=(-1)^{2}+\frac{2}{2}\in A$
\end_inset

.
 The 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{1}{100}$
\end_inset

-neighborhood about 
\begin_inset Formula $2$
