\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 contains no isolated points.
 To see this, let 
\begin_inset Formula $x\in B$
\end_inset

 and let 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon>0$
\end_inset

 be arbitrary.
 By the Density of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Q}$
\end_inset

 in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $V_{\epsilon}(x)$
\end_inset

 contains some point of 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{Q}$
\end_inset

, hence 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

