\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The limit points of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 are 
\begin_inset Formula $-1$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $1$
\end_inset

, and 
\begin_inset Formula $1=(-1)^{1}+\frac{2}{1}\in A$
\end_inset

.
 However, 
\begin_inset Formula $-1\notin A$
\end_inset

.
 For assume that it is; then 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
-1=(-1)^{n}+\frac{2}{n}\text{ for some }n\in\mathbb{N}.
\]

\end_inset

Subtracting 
\begin_inset Formula $(-1)^{n}$
\end_inset

 from both sides yields
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
-1-(-1)^{n} & =\frac{2}{n}\\
\implies\frac{2}{n} & =-2\text{ or 0}
\end{align*}

\end_inset

which is not true for any 
\begin_inset Formula $n\in\mathbb{N}$
\end_inset

.
 Therefore, 
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{A}=A\cup\{-1\}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
